    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-floor lineup, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** (74.07) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (72.39). **Gunnar Henderson** stands as our premier play; while Will Warren is a competent arm, the combination of **Gunnar Henderson**\u2019s elite lead-off efficiency and a favorable platoon matchup provides the highest raw ceiling of the day. Similarly, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** benefits from a soft matchup against Simeon Woods Richardson, where his high xwOBA suggests a breakout performance despite a slight dynamic platoon penalty. We are also capitalizing on high-variance spots, specifically in the outfield where **Josh Lowe** (71.68) draws an exceptional matchup against Christian Scott; the staggering 15.44 xERA assigned to Scott makes **Josh Lowe** an absolute must-start for potential power-speed production, serving as a pillar of our strategy to attack weak rotations.\n\nOur most difficult decision of the day involved **Marcell Ozuna** (58.45), who narrowly missed the starting cut despite a solid projection. While **Marcell Ozuna** benefits from favorable wind conditions against Brady Singer, the optimizer prioritized the positional flexibility and higher daily efficiency scores of **Dominic Smith** and **Nolan Schanuel** in the utility and outfield slots. We are monitoring **Heliot Ramos** (59.04) closely; although he is a priority start due to his sprint speed and the 100% SB probability against Shane McClanahan, his proximity to the 50-point threshold makes him our highest-risk asset today given the difficulty of the opposing pitcher. All managers should note that these rankings are predicated on pending lineups, particularly for **Drake Baldwin** and **Jacob Wilson**; should their projected spots in the #1 or #2 holes shift downward, we may see a correlated dip in their daily efficiency scores.",
